comment: by IUCN, 'The African Nile Crocodile is now recognized as two distinct species: one occupying eastern Africa, the Nile valley and southern Africa and retaining the name Crocodylus niloticus Laurenti, 1768; and the other occupying west and central Africa, including the Congo, Niger and Ogoue drainages and assigned to the existing name Crocodylus suchus Geoffroy, 1807 (Schmitz et al. 2003, Hekkala et al. 2011). Red List assessments now treat these two taxa independently.' However listing it here as we have a match and is extant in country, while Crocodylus suchus does not have a separate IUCN page!

comment: by IUCN, Varanus ornatus is a synonym of Varanus niloticus; the only other occurrences of ornatus are also as synonyms but for species not extant in CM; See also taxonomic notes from Varanus niloticus: "Although Böhme and Ziegler (1997) elevated Varanus niloticus ornatus, the large forest water monitor of the Congo Basin region, to full species status, a recent molecular analysis by Dowell et al. (2015) indicated that this taxon should be considered a junior synonym of V. niloticus. Varanus niloticus is likely to be a species complex whose taxonomy remains unresolved, but recovered three genetic distinct lineages, in the west, north and southern part of Africa  (Dowell et al. 2015)." Marking as Duplicate of 373 but expert opinion needed.
